<body>
<header>
  <div class="topbar">
    <div class="brand"><div class="logo">F&gt;_</div><div class="brand-copy"><h1>ForgRequest Web Console</h1><p>Manual HTTP replay and JavaScript-rendered page execution</p></div></div>
    <div class="top-actions"><span class="shortcut">Ctrl/⌘ + Enter</span><span class="version" id="version-pill">v</span><button type="button" class="btn btn-primary run-control" data-run-request><span>▶</span><span class="run-label">Run request</span></button></div>
  </div>
</header>
<div class="layout">
  <aside class="sidebar">
    <div class="side-label">Request workflow</div>
    <button type="button" class="tab active" data-panel="request"><span class="icon">01</span>Request</button>
    <button type="button" class="tab" data-panel="replay"><span class="icon">02</span>Replay & import</button>
    <button type="button" class="tab" data-panel="modifiers"><span class="icon">03</span>Modifiers & data</button>
    <button type="button" class="tab" data-panel="browser-network"><span class="icon">04</span>Browser & network</button>
    <button type="button" class="tab" data-panel="output"><span class="icon">05</span>Output & reports</button>
    <div class="side-label">Utilities</div>
    <button type="button" class="tab" data-panel="diff"><span class="icon">↔</span>Response diff</button>
    <button type="button" class="tab" data-panel="help"><span class="icon">?</span>Feature map</button>
    <div class="scope-note"><strong>Scope boundary</strong><br>One operator-supplied request or page navigation at a time. No crawling, discovery, scanning, or automatic link following.</div>
  </aside>
  <main class="content">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div><div class="eyebrow">ForgRequest operator console</div><h2>Replay HTTP precisely. Render JavaScript only when the page needs it.</h2><p>The standard requests engine remains the default. Browser mode opens one supplied GET URL in Chromium, Firefox, or WebKit, waits for the selected lifecycle condition, and captures the rendered DOM, console events, page errors, cookies, and storage state.</p></div>
        <div class="hero-badges"><div class="status-chip"><span>Selected engine</span><strong id="engine-status">HTTP</strong></div><div class="status-chip"><span>Browser runtime</span><strong id="browser-status">checking…</strong></div></div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="quick-summary"><div class="summary-item"><small>Method</small><strong id="summary-method">GET</strong></div><div class="summary-item"><small>Target</small><strong id="summary-url">Not configured</strong></div><div class="summary-item"><small>Request source</small><strong id="summary-source">Builder</strong></div><div class="summary-item"><small>Output</small><strong id="summary-output">Console</strong></div></section>

    <form id="request-form">
      <section id="request" class="panel active">
        <div class="section-head"><div><h2>Request builder</h2><p>Configure the target and request content.</p></div><span class="section-tag">Core</span></div>
        <div class="grid">
          <div class="card accent span12"><h3>Target</h3><p class="card-desc">The URL is operator supplied and is never stored in the default configuration.</p><div class="field-grid"><div class="field s3"><label class="field-label">Method</label><select name="method" id="method"><option>GET</option><option>POST</option><option>PUT</option><option>PATCH</option><option>DELETE</option><option>HEAD</option><option>OPTIONS</option><option>TRACE</option></select></div><div class="field s9"><label class="field-label">URL</label><input name="url" id="url" placeholder="https://example.com/api/resource"></div></div></div>
